{{afc comment|1=see history at [[every:Omodaru and Ayakashikone]][[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 09:17, 14 March 2025 (UTC)}}
{{Draft}} {{infobox deity|image=Uichini suichini shinbutsu-zue.jpg|temples={{ill|Dairokuten Shrine|lt=Dairokuten Shrines|ja|第六天神社|12=draft|12=draft}}|cult_center={{ill|Dairokuten Shrine|lt=Dairokuten Shrines|ja|第六天神社|12=draft|12=draft}}}} [[File:Japanese Primordial Deities-eng.svg|frame]] {{ill||Omodaru and Ayakashikone|ja|オモダル・アヤカシコネ}} is a pair of Japanese primordial deities<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Aragona |first=Jared |title=from Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697, Vol. 1 |url=https://open.maricopa.edu/worldmythologyvolume1godsandcreation/chapter/from-nihongi-chronicles-of-japan-from-the-earliest-times-to-a-d-697-vol-1/ |language=en}}</ref><ref name="heavens">{{Cite web |title=Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697, Volume 1 |url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Nihongi:_Chronicles_of_Japan_from_the_Earliest_Times_to_A.D._697/Book_I |via=Wikisource}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-04-11 |title=Encyclopedia of Shinto - Home : Kami in Classic Texts : Omodaru, Ayakashikone |url=http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=124 |access-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20210411072506/http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=124 |archive-date=2021-04-11 }}</ref><ref>https://archive.ph/a8w1z</ref>
They were preceded by {{ill||Otonoji and Otonobe|ja|オオトノヂ・オオトノベ}} and succeeded by [[Izanagi]] and [[Izanami]]
==Overview== {{Infobox deity | Name = Omotaru (淤母陀琉神) | Generation = {{ill|Seven Generations of the Divine Age|ja|神世七代|1=Kamiyonanayo|2=ja|3=神世七代|12=draft|12=draft}} Sixth Generation | Predecessor = {{ill|Ootonoji-Ootono be|ja|オオトノヂ・オオトノベ|lt=Itotonochi-no-Kami|lt_ja=意富斗能地神|12=draft|12=draft}} | Successor = {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|lt=Izanagi-no-Kami|lt_ja=伊邪那岐神|12=draft|12=draft}} | Deity Type = {{ill|Amatsukami-Kunitsukami|ja|天津神・国津神|lt=Amatsukami|lt_ja=天津神|12=draft|12=draft}} | Full Name = Omotaru-no-Kami (淤母陀琉神) | Alternate Names = Omotaru, Menashison, Menashihiko, Menotarami-no-Kami | Also Known As = | Divine Rank = | Divine Function = | Burial Place = | Father = | Mother = | Parentage = | Consort = | Children = | Shrine = | Associated Shrines = {{Plainlist| * {{ill|Sixth Heavenly Deity Shrine|ja|第六天神社|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kumano Hayatama Taisha|ja|熊野速玉大社|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Onda Shrine|ja|穏田神社|12=draft|12=draft}} 等 }} | Sources = {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}}、{{ill|Nihon Shoki|ja|日本書紀|12=draft|12=draft}} 等 | image = Omotaru kashikone shinbutsu-zue.jpg | image Description = (『Shinbutsu Zukai』) }}
