{{infobox deity|image=Uichini suichini shinbutsu-zue.jpg|temples={{ill|Dairokuten Shrine|lt=Dairokuten Shrines|ja|第六天神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dairokuten Shrine|qq=}}|cult_center={{ill|Dairokuten Shrine|lt=Dairokuten Shrines|ja|第六天神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Dairokuten Shrine|qq=}}}} [[File:Japanese Primordial Deities-eng.svg|frame]] {{ill|Omodaru and Ayakashikone|ja|オモダル・アヤカシコネ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omodaru and Ayakashikone|qq=}} is a pair of Japanese primordial deities<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Aragona |first=Jared |title=from Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697, Vol. 1 |url=https://open.maricopa.edu/worldmythologyvolume1godsandcreation/chapter/from-nihongi-chronicles-of-japan-from-the-earliest-times-to-a-d-697-vol-1/ |language=en}}</ref><ref name="heavens">{{Cite web |title=Nihongi: Chronicles of Japan from the Earliest Times to A.D. 697, Volume 1 |url=https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Nihongi:_Chronicles_of_Japan_from_the_Earliest_Times_to_A.D._697/Book_I |via=Wikisource}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-04-11 |title=Encyclopedia of Shinto - Home : Kami in Classic Texts : Omodaru, Ayakashikone |url=http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=124 |access-date=2023-03-22 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20210411072506/http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=124 |archive-date=2021-04-11 }}</ref><ref>https://archive.ph/a8w1z</ref>
They were preceded by {{ill|Otonoji and Otonobe|ja|オオトノヂ・オオトノベ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Otonoji and Otonobe|qq=}} and succeeded by [[Izanagi]] and [[Izanami]]
